     1â†’# Tailwind CSS + Astro + Vue 3 Best Practices (2024-2025)
     2â†’
     3â†’**Research Date:** 2025-10-22
     4â†’**Focus:** Configuration architecture, animations, SSR patterns, plugin design
     5â†’
     6â†’---
     7â†’
     8â†’## Executive Summary
     9â†’
    10â†’Tailwind CSS v4 introduced major architectural changes that fundamentally alter configuration patterns. The shift from `tailwind.config.js` to CSS-first configuration via `@theme` directive provides cleaner theme management, better type safety, and simplified multi-theme implementations. Astro + Vue 3 integration benefits from these patterns through improved SSR safety and hydration management.
    11â†’
    12â†’**Key Findings:**
    13â†’- Tailwind v4 uses `@theme` directive in CSS files instead of JavaScript config
    14â†’- `darkMode: "selector"` (v3) becomes `darkMode: "class"` for Astro SSR compatibility
    15â†’- Animation systems should centralize tokens via `@theme` with JavaScript/Vue integration via CSS variables
    16â†’- Custom utilities via `@utility` directive preferred over full plugins for most cases
    17â†’- Astro View Transitions require special dark mode persistence patterns
    18â†’
    19â†’---
    20â†’
    21â†’## 1. Tailwind Config Architecture
    22â†’
    23â†’### v4 Paradigm Shift: CSS-First Configuration
    24â†’
    25â†’**Source:** https://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme
    26â†’
    27â†’Tailwind v4 eliminates `tailwind.config.js` in favor of CSS-based configuration using the `@theme` directive.
    28â†’
    29â†’#### `@theme` Directive Fundamentals
    30â†’
    31â†’**Core difference from `:root`:**
    32â†’- `@theme` variables generate utility classes AND create CSS variables
    33â†’- `:root` variables are purely stylistic (no utilities generated)
    34â†’- Use `@theme` for design tokens, `:root` for internal CSS-only values
    35â†’
    36â†’**Theme Variable Namespaces:**
    37â†’
    38â†’| Namespace | Generated Utilities | Example |
    39â†’|-----------|-------------------|---------|
    40â†’| `--color-*` | `bg-`, `text-`, `border-`, `fill-` | `--color-primary: #3f3cbb` |
    41â†’| `--font-*` | `font-sans`, `font-serif` | `--font-display: Poppins, sans-serif` |
    42â†’| `--spacing-*` | `px-`, `py-`, `gap-`, `max-h-` | `--spacing-7: 1.75rem` |
    43â†’| `--radius-*` | `rounded-sm`, `rounded-lg` | `--radius-xl: 1rem` |
    44â†’| `--shadow-*` | `shadow-md`, `shadow-lg` | `--shadow-brutal: 4px 4px 0 #000` |
    45â†’| `--breakpoint-*` | `sm:*`, `md:*`, `lg:*` | `--breakpoint-tablet: 48rem` |
    46â†’
    47â†’#### Configuration Patterns
    48â†’
    49â†’**1. Extending Default Theme (Recommended for Most Cases):**
    50â†’
    51â†’```css
    52â†’@import "tailwindcss";
    53â†’
    54â†’@theme {
    55â†’  /* Adds to existing colors, doesn't replace */
    56â†’  --color-brand-primary: #3f3cbb;
    57â†’  --color-brand-secondary: #f59e0b;
    58â†’
    59â†’  /* Custom font families */
    60â†’  --font-display: Poppins, sans-serif;
    61â†’  --font-body: Inter, system-ui, sans-serif;
    62â†’
    63â†’  /* Custom spacing tokens */
    64â†’  --spacing-18: 4.5rem;
    65â†’  --spacing-128: 32rem;
    66â†’}
    67â†’```
    68â†’
    69â†’**2. Overriding Default Values:**
    70â†’
    71â†’```css
    72â†’@theme {
    73â†’  /* Changes existing breakpoint */
    74â†’  --breakpoint-sm: 30rem; /* was 40rem */
    75â†’
    76â†’  /* Replaces default shadow */
    77â†’  --shadow-xl: 0 20px 25px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    78â†’}
    79â†’```
    80â†’
    81â†’**3. Complete Namespace Replacement:**
    82â†’
    83â†’```css
    84â†’@theme {
    85â†’  /* Remove ALL default colors */
    86â†’  --color-*: initial;
    87â†’
    88â†’  /* Define only your custom palette */
    89â†’  --color-primary: #3f3cbb;
    90â†’  --color-secondary: #f59e0b;
    91â†’  --color-neutral-50: #fafafa;
    92â†’  --color-neutral-900: #171717;
    93â†’}
    94â†’```
    95â†’
    96â†’**âš ï¸ Warning:** Complete replacement removes utility classes like `bg-red-500`, `text-blue-600`, etc.
    97â†’
    98â†’#### Advanced Techniques
    99â†’
   100â†’**Referencing Other Variables:**
   101â†’
   102â†’```css
   103â†’@theme inline {
   104â†’  /* inline option prevents CSS variable resolution issues */
   105â†’  --font-sans: var(--font-inter);
   106â†’  --color-accent: var(--color-brand-primary);
   107â†’}
   108â†’```
   109â†’
   110â†’**Animation Keyframes in @theme:**
   111â†’
   112â†’```css
   113â†’@theme {
   114â†’  --animate-fade-in: fade-in 0.3s ease-out;
   115â†’  --animate-slide-up: slide-up 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
   116â†’
   117â†’  @keyframes fade-in {
   118â†’    from { opacity: 0; }
   119â†’    to { opacity: 1; }
   120â†’  }
   121â†’
   122â†’  @keyframes slide-up {
   123â†’    from { transform: translateY(1rem); opacity: 0; }
   124â†’    to { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 1; }
   125â†’  }
   126â†’}
   127â†’```
   128â†’
   129â†’**Sharing Across Projects (Monorepo Pattern):**
   130â†’
   131â†’```css
   132â†’/* packages/design-tokens/theme.css */
   133â†’@theme {
   134â†’  --color-brand-primary: #3f3cbb;
   135â†’  --color-brand-secondary: #f59e0b;
   136â†’  /* ... all shared tokens */
   137â†’}
   138â†’
   139â†’/* apps/marketing/styles/global.css */
   140â†’@import "@company/design-tokens/theme.css";
   141â†’@import "tailwindcss";
   142â†’```
   143â†’
   144â†’---
   145â†’
   146â†’## 2. Custom Color Palette Organization
   147â†’
   148â†’### Semantic Naming with Dark Mode Support
   149â†’
   150â†’**Source:** https://simonswiss.com/posts/tailwind-v4-multi-theme
   151â†’
   152â†’Tailwind v4 drastically simplifies multi-theme implementation by eliminating the need for RGB channel workarounds required in v3.
   153â†’
   154â†’#### v3 vs v4 Comparison
   155â†’
   156â†’**v3 Pattern (Complex, Error-Prone):**
   157â†’```javascript
   158â†’// tailwind.config.js
   159â†’module.exports = {
   160â†’  theme: {
   161â†’    colors: {
   162â†’      primary: 'rgb(var(--color-primary) / <alpha-value>)',
   163â†’    }
   164â†’  }
   165â†’}
   166â†’```
   167â†’```css
   168â†’:root {
   169â†’  --color-primary: 59 130 246; /* RGB channels only */
   170â†’}
   171â†’```
